00:06:57.710 --> 00:06:59.960
Some manner of cause
and effect relationship

00:06:59.960 --> 00:07:02.510
existed between the rise
of scientific knowledge

00:07:02.510 --> 00:07:04.250
and the decline of magic.

00:07:04.250 --> 00:07:07.070
The two could not
comfortably co-exist.

00:07:07.070 --> 00:07:10.460
To the extent that the database
could be cajoled into spitting

00:07:10.460 --> 00:07:13.160
out actual numbers, it
was clear that magic

00:07:13.160 --> 00:07:15.560
had declined gradually
but steadily starting

00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:17.729
in the middle of the 1600s.

00:07:17.729 --> 00:07:19.520
It was still holding
its own in the opening

00:07:19.520 --> 00:07:23.180
decades of the 1800s but
plunged into a nosedive

00:07:23.180 --> 00:07:24.980
during the 1830s.

00:07:24.980 --> 00:07:29.150
From then through the 1840s,
magic declined precipitously.

00:07:29.150 --> 00:07:32.870
As our store of documents, many
written by witches themselves,

00:07:32.870 --> 00:07:36.680
grew to fill a phalanx of used
filing cabinets and gun safes

00:07:36.680 --> 00:07:38.630
that Tristan scored
on Craigslist,

00:07:38.630 --> 00:07:40.310
we were able to
track the decline

00:07:40.310 --> 00:07:43.070
from year to year and
then from month to month.

00:07:43.070 --> 00:07:45.530
These poor women expressed
shock at the dwindling

00:07:45.530 --> 00:07:49.340
of their powers, in some cases,
mentioning specific spells

00:07:49.340 --> 00:07:53.390
that had worked a few weeks
ago but no longer had effect.

00:07:53.390 --> 00:07:56.960
As it turns out, in 1851, the
year in which I find myself

00:07:56.960 --> 00:08:00.020
as I scribble these words, all
of the world's technologies

00:08:00.020 --> 00:08:02.330
were brought together
for the Great Exhibition

00:08:02.330 --> 00:08:04.580
at the newly constructed
magnificent Crystal

00:08:04.580 --> 00:08:07.640
Palace in Hyde Park, London.

00:08:07.640 --> 00:08:09.920
Tristan's hypothesis,
therefore, held

00:08:09.920 --> 00:08:12.740
that this coming together,
this conscious concentration

00:08:12.740 --> 00:08:16.820
of technological advancement
all in one point of spacetime

00:08:16.820 --> 00:08:20.540
had dampened magic to the point,
where it fizzled out for good.

00:08:20.540 --> 00:08:22.490
Like a doused fire,
it had no power

00:08:22.490 --> 00:08:25.190
to rekindle itself
once extinguished.

00:08:25.190 --> 00:08:28.850
The causal relationship between
the two eluded us for a time.

00:08:28.850 --> 00:08:31.430
I suggested that magic's
flourishing required people

00:08:31.430 --> 00:08:34.340
to believe in it, but Tristan
dismissed this mentality

00:08:34.340 --> 00:08:37.520
as belonging more to children's
literature than to reality.

00:08:37.520 --> 00:08:40.010
He was certain there was
a mechanical or physical

00:08:40.010 --> 00:08:42.080
causality, that
there was something

00:08:42.080 --> 00:08:45.620
about the technological world
view or technology itself

00:08:45.620 --> 00:08:48.740
that somehow jammed the
frequencies magic used.

00:08:48.740 --> 00:08:51.260
We both began to read whatever
we could about the Great

00:08:51.260 --> 00:08:54.980
Exhibition in the hopes that
it might illuminate something.

00:08:54.980 --> 00:08:56.480
You may notice that
I was exceeding

00:08:56.480 --> 00:08:59.240
by far my responsibilities
as a translator.

00:08:59.240 --> 00:09:01.610
Translating especially
of obscure texts

00:09:01.610 --> 00:09:04.340
written in extinct
tongues often resembles

00:09:04.340 --> 00:09:05.870
the solving of a riddle.

00:09:05.870 --> 00:09:08.810
Here was a riddle to
put all others to shame.

00:09:08.810 --> 00:09:10.700
Tristan's enthusiasm
was infectious,

00:09:10.700 --> 00:09:12.680
