divest myself from it.

00:09:12.680 --> 00:09:14.390
Having no other
responsibilities,

00:09:14.390 --> 00:09:17.896
I became as preoccupied with
his project as he was himself.

00:09:17.896 --> 00:09:21.080
Per Tristan's suggestion,
I took out stacks of books

00:09:21.080 --> 00:09:22.430
from Widener Library.

00:09:22.430 --> 00:09:25.190
Harvard had not figured
out yet that I'd quit.

00:09:25.190 --> 00:09:27.980
These included tomes on
everything from heliography

00:09:27.980 --> 00:09:30.980
to Queen Victoria's private
life to Baruch Spinoza's

00:09:30.980 --> 00:09:33.380
sexual proclivities
to Frederick Bakewell

00:09:33.380 --> 00:09:36.470
to the tempest prognosticator
to Strewhall numbers.

00:09:36.470 --> 00:09:38.060
I would bring these
to Tristan, and we

00:09:38.060 --> 00:09:40.190
would divide our time
between perusing them

00:09:40.190 --> 00:09:41.750
and internet searches.

00:09:41.750 --> 00:09:46.040
