Great Exhibition and its 13,000

00:09:46.040 --> 00:09:48.680
odd exhibits than
Prince Albert ever did.

00:09:48.680 --> 00:09:51.560
We knew more about its
showcase, the Crystal Palace,

00:09:51.560 --> 00:09:53.540
than even Joseph
Paxton, the gardener

00:09:53.540 --> 00:09:55.790
who designed the blessed thing.

00:09:55.790 --> 00:09:57.840
We learned little
that was helpful.

00:09:57.840 --> 00:09:59.720
However, one evening
in March, as I

00:09:59.720 --> 00:10:01.550
sat on the consignment
store couch

00:10:01.550 --> 00:10:04.190
I'd insisted on bringing
into spruce up the place,

00:10:04.190 --> 00:10:07.910
and Tristan lolled on the rug
beside a low table with a beer,

00:10:07.910 --> 00:10:09.980
each of us bleary-eyed
from reading,

00:10:09.980 --> 00:10:13.250
I encountered a passage in
an obscure booklet entitled,

00:10:13.250 --> 00:10:16.250
"Arresting and Alluring
Astronomical Anecdotes,"

00:10:16.250 --> 00:10:18.500
published in 1897.

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:21.200
